tspan.tspan: Stretch
Goals
We will optimize game performance through a
combination of hardware upgrades, software upgrades,
and good ol' fashioned analysis and refactoring.
The NPC population of Settlements
in Brunelleschi will be expanded to
track their distinct homes, jobs,
happiness, and new personal traits.
They will get representative animations and pathing for
work, leisure, happiness, and unhappiness to give each
settlement a feel of thriving, churning life.
Supporters who have donated
$50 or more will be able to vote
for any of the expansions
remaining from any of the
previously listed sets.
We will throw an actual Masquerade Ball in an actual
local Ballroom. The first 200 Supporters who have
donated $100 or more to RSVP will be sent invitations
covering the event itself (we will not be able to provide
for travel or lodging expenses). All Supporters will
receive a digital 'Thank You' from us in costume at the
event.
We will expand the magic system of the game to offer
more nuance and depth. Schools of magic will be
introduced with their own advancement paths and Spells
will generate a variety of effects beyond their ability to
adjust the user's attributes and influence combat.
We will expand the Religion system of the game to offer
more nuance and depth. Religion based advancement
paths will be introduced, each with its own set of Spells,
and actions.
Supporters who have donated
$50 or more will be able to vote
for any of the expansions
remaining from any of the
previously listed sets.
